Watirloo, a Watir Framework and Helper based on Page Objects Modeling

== Watirloo Summary

Semantic Test Objects Modeling in Watir

A Helper Framework to design tests based 
on semantic naming of Page Objects 
rather than their DOM implementation.

rake test runs tests. Give it a try.

== Requirements

gem install watir

== Install

download it. it's not a gem yet

== Changes

version 0.0.1

* radio_group method added to Watir (not to FireWatir yet)
* tests can run on IE and Firefox (see Rakefile)
* patch fof Firefox.attach to just attach to the latest window without starting new ff win.
* added extra dir for some experimetns
* added examles dir for experiments with Watir
* added ruby_study dir for demonstrating ruby methods in the context of test/spec runner


=== Roadmap

Towards version 0.0.2

* make Watirloo agnostic to browser IE or Firefox or Safari
* make tests run on IE, Firefox, Safari with the same interface
* create radio_group to behave like select list and checkbox_group like multi select list
* build UseCase class as template for scenario based execution of tests for exploratory testing

